metadata.description: “PARADE” was my second release this year. It talks about personal growth and the desire to leave your old life behind. It describes the feeling of betrayal you experience when dealing with snakes in the grass, exes and old friends appear out of nowhere at the sight of success.

lyrics.text:
Don’t talk don’t wait
I saw you yesterday
I heard you call my name
I went the other way
The other way
So don’t say
That you’re in love with me
You’re my worst enemy
You make me go insane 
You always rain on my parade
I don’t wanna be your lover so leave me alone
Stop dialling up my numbers yeah stop calling my phone
I’m never gonna pick up when you call me no no
Won’t fall for this again so leave your message at the tone

Don’t go and rain on my parade
Don’t go and rain on mine
I want none of your time
Don’t go and rain on my parade
Don’t go and rain on mine
I want none of your time
Don’t go and rain on mine

Girl are you trying to get under my skin yeah
How do you know exactly where I’ve been huh
My fingernails are coming loose from my fingertips 
I see straight through all the lies so don’t go rain on my parade

Don’t go and rain on mine
I want none of your time
Don’t go and rain on my parade
Don’t go and rain on mine
I want none of your time
Don’t go and rain on mine
